                    <msContents>
                        <summary>This Persian translation of the <title>Wonders of Creation</title>, Qazvīnī's famous medieval Arabic cosmography, contains 405 illustrations that depict a wide range of curious, animated, and amusing subjects. 
                            While incomplete, it closely comports with another volume held in the British Library (Add. 23564) completed in 845 AH (1441 CE) in Muzaffarid-era Shiraz (see Titley no. 238).
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_37-item1">
